The paper discusses the development and testing of a mobile application for collaborative learning, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HCI), machine learning (ML), and educational technology (ET). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which encompasses research on the social and ethical implications of computing technologies. The paper also focuses on usability testing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and development of a collaborative learning application, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of ML techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile technology for educational purposes, which falls under the sub-category of cs.ET (Educational Technology).
